Consider the proof of `indepFun_fst_add_one_hist`. We need to show that the $(n+1)$-th randomization variable $\omega.1(n+1)$ is independent of the history up to time $n$, $\text{hist alg } \omega \ n$, under the measure `arrayMeasure ν`.

The measure `arrayMeasure ν` is a product measure $\mu_1 \otimes \mu_2$, where $\mu_1$ is an infinite product of uniform measures on $I$, and $\mu_2$ is the stream measure.
Let $X(\omega) = \omega.1(n+1)$. Let $Y(\omega) = \text{hist alg } \omega \ n$.
$X$ depends only on the $(n+1)$-th coordinate of the first component.
$Y$ depends on the coordinates $0, \dots, n$ of the first component and on the second component.
Since $\mu_1$ is a product measure, the coordinate $n+1$ is independent of the coordinates $0, \dots, n$.
Also, the first component is independent of the second component in a product measure.
Thus $X$ is independent of $Y$.

